    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 19,
        "summary": "David testifies, The heavens declare the glory of God, the law of the Lord is perfect, and the judgments of the Lord are true and righteous altogether.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The heavens declare the glory of God; and the firmament sheweth his handywork.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heaven; Nature, Earth.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 50:6.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory; God, Glory of.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 104:14.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Day unto day uttereth speech, and night unto night sheweth knowledge.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "There is no speech nor language, where their voice is not heard.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Language.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Their line is gone out through all the earth, and their words to the end of the world. In them hath he set a tabernacle for the sun,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 10:18; 2\u00a0Ne. 31:15; D&C 64:31.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Which is as a bridegroom coming out of his chamber, and rejoiceth as a strong man to run a race.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "His going forth is from the end of the heaven, and his circuit unto the ends of it: and there is nothing hid from the heat thereof.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The law of the Lord is perfect, converting the soul: the testimony of the Lord is sure, making wise the simple.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abundant Life; God, Law of.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Perfection.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conversion; Scriptures, Value of.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Testimony.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 32:34 (32\u201334).",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 116:6.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The statutes of the Lord are right, rejoicing the heart: the commandment of the Lord is pure, enlightening the eyes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cheerful.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 12:6.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Edification.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of the Lord is clean, enduring for ever: the judgments of the Lord are true and righteous altogether.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 34:12; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:15; 30:9.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Truth.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 725
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "More to be desired are they than gold, yea, than much fine gold: sweeter also than honey and the honeycomb.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:127.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:72.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover by them is thy servant warned: and in keeping of them there is great reward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Warn.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 2:22; D&C 14:7; 58:2.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Who can understand his errors? cleanse thou me from secret faults.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Purification.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 90:8; D&C 1:3.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Keep back thy servant also from presumptuous sins; let them not have dominion over me: then shall I be upright, and I shall be innocent from the great transgression.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:133.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the words of my mouth, and the meditation of my heart, be acceptable in thy sight, O Lord, my strength, and my redeemer.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meditation.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strength.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
